SIMPLE: systemless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Systemless
<hw>Sys"tem*less</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Being without
system.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Nat. Hist.)</fld> <def>Not agreeing with some
artificial system of classification.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Not having any of the distinct
systems or types of structure, as the radiate, articulate, etc.,
characteristic of organic nature; <as>as, all unicellular organisms are
<ex>systemless</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Systole</ent>⟦br⟧
